## Base64Encoder
Python requires to import image to display in tkinter but also image data can be used to display image in tkinter (without importing!)

# Objective
1.The main objective of the application is to copy the Base64 data of the .gif file selected.                                           
2.This allows the user to save the QR Code once the desired data is shown.                                                               
3.This provides a good UI for the user to work with.                                                                                       

# Installation
Use the package manager [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/) to install packages.

```bash
pip install pyperclip
```

# Usage
```python
import base64
import tkinter
from tkinter import *

top = tkinter.Tk()
top.title("Test app")

dats =''''''

imagePath = PhotoImage(data=dats)
widgetf = Label(top,  image=imagePath,  bg="#3399ff")
widgetf.place(x=0, y=0)

top.geometry("480x350")
top.update()
top.mainloop()

```
# Warning!
1. Use only gif files otherwise it won't work!
2. remove 'b' in the beginning of the data and enclose the data in three Quotation marks i.e. '''{data}'''
